<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 05-12-05 - New Piston Cooling Tube</stitle>
    <tsi id="tSI051205" year="2005" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>05-12-05</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>March 2005</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>New Piston Cooling Tube</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>DT 466
                    <snrange>2000001 and up</snrange>
                </engfam>
                <engfam>DT 570
                    <snrange>2000001 and up</snrange>
                </engfam>
                <engfam>HT 570
                    <snrange>2000001 and up</snrange>
                </engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>A new piston cooling tube has been released that is lighter while increasing its structural
                    stiffness. The old piston cooling tube mounting bracket was machined from block steel (Figure 1).
                    The new piston cooling tube has a stamped steel bracket (Figure 2), an O-ring on the underside
                    (Figure 3) and comes in a kit that also includes a bolt. Do not use an old bolt with the new piston
                    cooling tube. The new piston cooling tube is a direct drop-in replacement and will be available in
                    April 2005. The old piston cooling tube will continue to be issued from parts service until supply
                    is exhausted.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Make sure you use the mounting bolt that comes with the kit instead of the old bolt.
                            Failing to do so may result in the bolt loosening over time resulting in severe engine
                            damage.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <para>The new piston cooling tube comes in two variations, knurled (Figure 2) and non-knurled. The
                    piston cooling tubes
                    <emph type="bold">with knurling</emph>
                    are used on the DT 570 and HT 570 engines while the piston cooling tubes
                    <emph type="bold">without knurling</emph>
                    are used on the DT 466 engines. The knurled and non-knurled tubes have different flow rates. Thus,
                    it is critical to ensure that you use the correct piston cooling tube on your engine, or severe
                    engine damage will result.
                </para>
